Certainly! Here is an example of how the database structure using Mongoose could look like for a game of hearts:

1. A schema for the player collection:

```javascript
const mongoose = require('mongoose');
const Schema = mongoose.Schema;

const playerSchema = new Schema({
  name: String,
  hand: [String],
  trickHistory: [{
    trickNum: Number,
    cards: [String]
  }],
  points: Number
});

const Player = mongoose.model('Player', playerSchema);

module.exports = Player;
```

2. A schema for the overall game state collection:

```javascript
const mongoose = require('mongoose');
const Schema = mongoose.Schema;

const gameStateSchema = new Schema({
  players: [{
    playerId: {
      type: Schema.Types.ObjectId,
      ref: 'Player'
    },
    score: Number
  }],
  currentTrick: {
    trickNum: Number,
    cards: [String]
  },
  cardsPlayed: [String],
  round: Number
});

const GameState = mongoose.model('GameState', gameStateSchema);

module.exports = GameState;
```

The 'ref' field in the 'players' array allows you to reference the Player schema when querying data on the game state collection.

